description: [``botocore``] AWS AppConfig now supports dynamic parameters, which enhance the functionality of AppConfig Extensions by allowing you to provide parameter values to your Extensions at the time you deploy your configuration.
[``botocore``] This release adds an optional parameter to RegisterImage and CopyImage APIs to support tagging AMIs at the time of creation.
[``botocore``] Adds support for the new GrafanaToken as part of the Amazon Managed Grafana Enterprise plugins upgrade to associate your AWS account with a Grafana Labs account.
[``botocore``] AWS Payment Cryptography EMV Decrypt Feature  Release
[``botocore``] Updates Amazon RDS documentation for io2 storage for Multi-AZ DB clusters
[``botocore``] Doc-only update for change to EKS-Anywhere ordering.

[``botocore``] You can increase the max request body inspection size for some regional resources. The size setting is in the web ACL association config. Also, the AWSManagedRulesBotControlRuleSet EnableMachineLearning setting now takes a Boolean instead of a primitive boolean type, for languages like Java.
